text: Arthur Champernowne (1580–c. 1650), of Dartington, near Totnes, Devon was an English politician. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of England for Totnes in 1624 and 1626.http://historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1604-1629/member/champernowne- arthur-1580-1650 He was buried in the old parish church at Dartington. ==References== Category:1580 births Category:1650 deaths Category:Members of the Parliament of England (pre-1707) for Totnes Category:English MPs 1624–1625 Category:English MPs 1626
